Run:
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:gns3/ppa
sudo apt update
sudo apt install gns3-gui gns3-server


During install:
- if asked about Wireshark, answer Yes
- if asked about ubridge, answer Yes


Then add your user to the useful groups:
sudo usermod -aG ubridge,libvirt,kvm,wireshark,docker "$USER"


Then log out and log back in.
To start GNS3


Desktop GUI:
gns3

Server only:
gns3server

If you want to test the server/web side after that:
curl http://127.0.0.1:3080/v2/version

If it works, GNS3 server is listening on port 3080.
Browser URL if the web UI/server is exposed:
http://127.0.0.1:3080

Recommended extra packages
For Docker-based labs and captures, these are often useful too:
sudo apt install dynamips ubridge wireshark
ubridge is especially important for GNS3 networking.